The workshop wanted to emphasize an interdisciplinary dialogue, bridge the gap between theory and practice, and encourage knowledge exchange between academics, policymakers, citizens, and activists.

1. More than 50 active participants attended the workshop.

2. Another direct outcome was the preparation and the acceptance of the Special Session entitled 'Beyond Smart &amp;amp; Data-Driven City-Regions? Rethinking Stakeholder-Helixes Strategies' between Dr Igor Calzada, MBA, from the Urban Transformations ESRC programme, and Dr Paul Cowie, from the Future Cities Catapult and the Urban Transformations ESRC programme, for the RSA (Regional Studies Association) Annual Congress 2017 on 4-7th June 2017. 
